@*
 * ============================================================================
 * DotNet Bookstore — In-Class ASP.NET Core MVC Project
 * Course: COMP2084 | Georgian College | Summer 2026
 * Instructor: Dario Hesami
 * ============================================================================
 *
 * FILE:    Views/_ViewImports.cshtml
 * PURPOSE: Declares global @using namespaces and enables Tag Helpers for
 *          EVERY Razor view in the application. You do not need to repeat
 *          these lines in individual views.
 *
 * KEY CONCEPTS FOR STUDENTS:
 *  1. @using             — makes a C# namespace available in all views, just
 *                          like "using" at the top of a .cs file.
 *                          "DotNetBookstore" → access to any class in the root namespace.
 *                          "DotNetBookstore.Models" → access to Book, Category, etc.
 *                          without needing the full namespace path in each view.
 *  2. @addTagHelper      — enables a set of Tag Helpers in all views.
 *                          Tag Helpers are C# classes that look like HTML attributes
 *                          (e.g., asp-for, asp-controller, asp-action) but run
 *                          server-side and generate proper HTML output.
 *          "*, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers" — the asterisk (*) imports
 *          ALL built-in ASP.NET Core Tag Helpers in one line. Common ones:
 *            asp-controller / asp-action / asp-area → generate href/action URLs
 *            asp-for                                → binds an input to a model property
 *            asp-validation-for                     → shows validation error messages
 *            asp-validation-summary                 → shows all model-level errors
 *            asp-items                              → populates a <select> with options
 *            asp-append-version                     → cache-busts static file URLs
 * ============================================================================
 *@

@* Make the root application namespace available in all views *@
@using DotNetBookstore

@* Make the Models namespace available so views can reference Book, Category, etc.
   directly without writing DotNetBookstore.Models.Book every time *@
@using DotNetBookstore.Models

@* Enable all built-in ASP.NET Core Tag Helpers (asp-*, etc.) in all views *@
@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers
